---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const title = "Edibles vs Smoking Cannabis | Comparison Guide 2026";
const description = "Compare edibles vs smoking cannabis in Australia. Onset times, duration, dosing & health effects explained. Find which method suits you best.";

const blogSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  "headline": title,
  "description": description,
  "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Mullaways Medical Cannabis", "url": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Mullaways Medical Cannabis", "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/logo.png" } },
  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-01-01",
  "mainEntityOfPage": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/blog/edibles-vs-smoking",
  "image": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/og-default.png"
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Blog", "item": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/blog" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Edibles vs Smoking", "item": "https://mullawaysmedicalcannabis.com.au/blog/edibles-vs-smoking" }
  ]
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} schema={[blogSchema, breadcrumbSchema]} ogType="article">
  <Header />
  
  <main>
    <Breadcrumb items={[{label: 'Home', href: '/'}, {label: 'Blog', href: '/blog'}, {label: 'Edibles vs Smoking'}]} />
    <article class="blog-article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="header-content">
            <span class="category">Education</span>
            <h1>Edibles vs Smoking Cannabis: Which is Better?</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">A comprehensive comparison of the two most popular consumption methods</p>
            <div class="meta">
              <span>By Mullaways Medical Team</span>
              <span>•</span>
              <span>Updated January 2026</span>
              <span>•</span>
              <span>8 min read</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="article-content">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <!-- Introduction -->
          <div class="intro-text">
            <p>When it comes to consuming cannabis, two methods dominate: <strong>edibles</strong> and <strong>smoking</strong>. Each offers distinct experiences, benefits, and considerations. Understanding the differences can help you choose the method that best suits your needs and lifestyle.</p>
            <p>This guide compares <strong>cannabis edibles</strong> (including gummies, baked goods, and infused foods) with smoking (flower, pre-rolls) across key factors like onset time, duration, dosing, and health considerations.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
          <section>
            <h2>Quick Comparison Chart</h2>
            <div class="table-wrap">
              <table class="comparison-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Factor</th>
                    <th><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 1 0 10 10 4 4 0 0 1-5-5 4 4 0 0 1-5-5"/><path d="M8.5 8.5v.01"/><path d="M16 15.5v.01"/><path d="M12 12v.01"/><path d="M11 17v.01"/><path d="M7 14v.01"/></svg> Edibles</th>
                    <th><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 12H3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h14"/><path d="M18 8c0-2.5-2-2.5-2-5"/><path d="M22 8c0-2.5-2-2.5-2-5"/><path d="M18 12v4"/><path d="M22 12v4"/></svg> Smoking</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr><td><strong>Onset Time</strong></td><td>30 min - 2 hours</td><td>Immediate - 10 min</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Duration</strong></td><td>4-8+ hours</td><td>1-3 hours</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Intensity</strong></td><td>Often stronger, body-focused</td><td>Controllable, head-focused</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Dosing Ease</strong></td><td>Pre-dosed, consistent</td><td>Variable, harder to measure</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Discretion</strong></td><td>Very discreet</td><td>Noticeable smell</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Lung Health</strong></td><td>No lung exposure</td><td>Potential irritation</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>Beginner Friendly</strong></td><td><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3Z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg> Caution needed</td><td>✓ Easier to control</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- How Each Method Works -->
          <section>
            <h2>How Each Method Works</h2>
            <div class="comparison-grid">
              <div class="card card-orange">
                <h3><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 1 0 10 10 4 4 0 0 1-5-5 4 4 0 0 1-5-5"/><path d="M8.5 8.5v.01"/><path d="M16 15.5v.01"/><path d="M12 12v.01"/><path d="M11 17v.01"/><path d="M7 14v.01"/></svg> How Edibles Work</h3>
                <p>When you eat cannabis, it travels through your digestive system to your liver. There, THC is converted into <strong>11-hydroxy-THC</strong>, a metabolite that's actually more potent and crosses the blood-brain barrier more effectively.</p>
                <p>This process explains why edibles often feel stronger and last longer than smoked cannabis—your body creates a more powerful version of THC during digestion.</p>
                <div class="card-highlight card-highlight-orange">
                  <strong>The Journey:</strong><br/>
                  Mouth → Stomach → Liver (conversion) → Bloodstream → Brain
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="card card-blue">
                <h3><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 12H3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h14"/><path d="M18 8c0-2.5-2-2.5-2-5"/><path d="M22 8c0-2.5-2-2.5-2-5"/><path d="M18 12v4"/><path d="M22 12v4"/></svg> How Smoking Works</h3>
                <p>When you inhale cannabis smoke, THC passes through your lungs and enters your bloodstream directly. From there, it travels to your brain within seconds, producing almost immediate effects.</p>
                <p>Because the THC bypasses your liver initially, it reaches your brain as <strong>Delta-9-THC</strong> rather than the more potent 11-hydroxy-THC, resulting in a different type of high.</p>
                <div class="card-highlight card-highlight-blue">
                  <strong>The Journey:</strong><br/>
                  Lungs → Bloodstream → Brain (almost instantly)
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Onset and Duration -->
          <section>
            <h2>Onset Time and Duration</h2>
            <div class="timeline-card">
              <h3><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg> Edibles Timeline</h3>
              <div class="timeline-row">
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value orange">30-90 min</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">First effects</span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-bar orange"></div>
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value orange">2-3 hours</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">Peak effects</span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-bar orange"></div>
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value orange">4-8+ hours</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">Total duration</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p><strong>Important:</strong> Many people make the mistake of taking more edibles because they don't feel effects quickly. Always wait at least 2 hours before considering additional doses.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="timeline-card">
              <h3><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg> Smoking Timeline</h3>
              <div class="timeline-row">
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value blue">Seconds</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">First effects</span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-bar blue"></div>
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value blue">15-30 min</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">Peak effects</span>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-bar blue"></div>
                <div class="timeline-point">
                  <span class="timeline-value blue">1-3 hours</span>
                  <span class="timeline-label">Total duration</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p>The quick onset allows for easier dose control. You can take a puff, wait a few minutes to assess effects, and decide whether to continue.</p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- The Experience -->
          <section>
            <h2>The Experience: How They Feel Different</h2>
            <div class="comparison-grid">
              <div class="card card-orange">
                <h3>Edibles High</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li>✓ More <strong>body-focused</strong> experience</li>
                  <li>✓ Often described as "heavier" or more "full-body"</li>
                  <li>✓ Can feel more psychedelic at higher doses</li>
                  <li>✓ More sedating for many users</li>
                  <li>✓ Better for long-lasting relief</li>
                  <li>✓ May help with sleep due to duration</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="card card-blue">
                <h3>Smoking High</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li>✓ More <strong>head-focused</strong> experience</li>
                  <li>✓ Often described as "lighter" or "cleaner"</li>
                  <li>✓ Easier to remain functional</li>
                  <li>✓ Strain-specific effects more noticeable</li>
                  <li>✓ Better for social situations</li>
                  <li>✓ Easier to dose for desired intensity</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Dosing Guide -->
          <section>
            <h2>Dosing Guidelines</h2>
            <div class="warning-box">
              <h4><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3Z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg> The Golden Rule of Edibles</h4>
              <p>"Start low, go slow." This is especially important with edibles because once you've consumed too much, you'll need to wait several hours for effects to subside. There's no quick fix for an edible that's too strong.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Edibles Dosing Chart (THC)</h3>
            <div class="table-wrap">
              <table class="comparison-table table-orange">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Dose</th>
                    <th>Experience Level</th>
                    <th>Effects</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr><td><strong>1-2.5mg</strong></td><td>Microdose</td><td>Mild relief, enhanced focus, minimal impairment</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>2.5-5mg</strong></td><td>Beginner</td><td>Noticeable relaxation, slight euphoria</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>5-15mg</strong></td><td>Intermediate</td><td>Stronger euphoria, impaired coordination</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>15-30mg</strong></td><td>Experienced</td><td>Strong effects, significant impairment</td></tr>
                  <tr><td><strong>30mg+</strong></td><td>High Tolerance</td><td>Very strong, for experienced users only</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Health Considerations -->
          <section>
            <h2>Health Considerations</h2>
            <div class="comparison-grid">
              <div class="info-card">
                <h3 class="green">✓ Edibles Advantages</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>No lung exposure:</strong> No smoke or vapor in your respiratory system</li>
                  <li><strong>Longer relief:</strong> Extended duration ideal for chronic conditions</li>
                  <li><strong>Precise dosing:</strong> Pre-measured doses for consistency</li>
                  <li><strong>Discretion:</strong> No smell, looks like regular food</li>
                  <li><strong>No equipment:</strong> No need for papers, pipes, or lighters</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h3 class="red"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3Z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg> Edibles Risks</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Overconsumption:</strong> Easy to take too much while waiting for effects</li>
                  <li><strong>Delayed onset:</strong> Hard to gauge proper dose initially</li>
                  <li><strong>Longer duration:</strong> If uncomfortable, effects last hours</li>
                  <li><strong>Digestive variability:</strong> Effects vary based on what else you've eaten</li>
                  <li><strong>Calorie content:</strong> Many edibles contain sugar and calories</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h3 class="green">✓ Smoking Advantages</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Immediate onset:</strong> Effects felt within minutes</li>
                  <li><strong>Easy dose control:</strong> Can stop when desired effect is reached</li>
                  <li><strong>Shorter duration:</strong> Effects wear off in 1-3 hours</li>
                  <li><strong>Strain effects:</strong> Terpene profiles are more noticeable</li>
                  <li><strong>Quick relief:</strong> Ideal for acute symptoms</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h3 class="red"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3Z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg> Smoking Risks</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Respiratory effects:</strong> Smoke can irritate lungs</li>
                  <li><strong>Carcinogens:</strong> Combustion creates harmful compounds</li>
                  <li><strong>Smell:</strong> Very noticeable odor</li>
                  <li><strong>Not discreet:</strong> Obvious when consuming</li>
                  <li><strong>Variable quality:</strong> Inconsistent dosing with flower</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Which is Right for You -->
          <section>
            <h2>Which Method is Right for You?</h2>
            <div class="card card-orange">
              <h3>Choose Edibles If You...</h3>
              <ul class="check-grid">
                <li>✓ Want to avoid smoking</li>
                <li>✓ Need long-lasting effects</li>
                <li>✓ Prefer discreet consumption</li>
                <li>✓ Have respiratory concerns</li>
                <li>✓ Want precise, consistent doses</li>
                <li>✓ Are treating chronic conditions</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-blue">
              <h3>Choose Smoking If You...</h3>
              <ul class="check-grid">
                <li>✓ Want immediate effects</li>
                <li>✓ Need quick symptom relief</li>
                <li>✓ Prefer shorter duration</li>
                <li>✓ Want more control over dosing</li>
                <li>✓ Enjoy the ritual experience</li>
                <li>✓ Want to experience specific strains</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-purple">
              <h3>Consider Both If You...</h3>
              <ul class="check-grid">
                <li>✓ Have varying needs throughout the day</li>
                <li>✓ Want flexibility in consumption</li>
                <li>✓ Are managing different symptoms</li>
                <li>✓ Like variety in your experience</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- CTA Section -->
          <div class="cta-box">
            <h3>Explore Our Product Range</h3>
            <p>Whether you prefer edibles, flower, or want to try both, we have quality options to suit your needs.</p>
            <div class="cta-buttons">
              <a href="/shop/edibles" class="btn btn-white">Shop Edibles →</a>
              <a href="/shop" class="btn btn-outline">View All Products →</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ Section -->
          <section>
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
              <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Why do edibles feel stronger than smoking?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">When you eat cannabis, your liver converts THC into 11-hydroxy-THC, which is more potent and crosses the blood-brain barrier more effectively. This metabolite produces stronger, more psychoactive effects compared to the delta-9-THC that reaches your brain when smoking.</div>
              </details>
              <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Can I eat edibles and smoke on the same day?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">Yes, but be cautious. The effects can compound, leading to an unexpectedly strong experience. If you choose to combine methods, reduce your typical dose of each and wait to assess total effects before consuming more.</div>
              </details>
              <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>What should I do if I've eaten too much edibles?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">Stay calm—this will pass. Find a comfortable, safe place to rest. Stay hydrated, try to eat something light, and distract yourself with calming activities. Some people find that CBD can help counteract THC's effects. Most importantly, remember that no one has ever died from cannabis overconsumption.</div>
              </details>
              <details class="faq-item">
                <summary>Are edibles healthier than smoking?</summary>
                <div class="faq-answer">From a respiratory standpoint, yes—edibles don't expose your lungs to smoke. However, both methods have considerations. Edibles often contain sugar and calories, and it's easier to accidentally overconsume. The "healthiest" method depends on your individual health concerns and how responsibly you consume.</div>
              </details>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Related Articles -->
          <div class="related-posts">
            <h3>Related Articles</h3>
            <div class="related-grid">
              <a href="/blog/cannabis-prices-australia" class="related-card">
                <span><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M16 8h-6a2 2 0 1 0 0 4h4a2 2 0 1 1 0 4H8"/><path d="M12 18V6"/></svg></span>
                <h4>Cannabis Prices in Australia 2026</h4>
                <p>Complete guide to weed prices across Australia.</p>
              </a>
              <a href="/blog/strongest-strains-australia" class="related-card">
                <span><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M11 20A7 7 0 0 1 9.8 6.9C15.5 4.9 17 3.5 19 2c1 2 2 4.5 2 8 0 5.5-4.5 10-10 10Z"/><path d="M2 21c0-3 1.85-5.36 5.08-6C9.5 14.52 12 13 13 12"/></svg></span>
                <h4>10 Strongest Strains in Australia</h4>
                <p>Explore the most potent cannabis strains for experienced users.</p>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-eucalyptus) 0%, var(--color-sage) 100%);
    padding: 40px 0 60px;
    color: white;
  }
  .header-content { max-width: 800px; }
